theorem P1_iff_closure_interior_eq_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 A ↔ closure (interior A) = closure A := by
  constructor
  · intro hP1
    dsimp [Topology.P1] at hP1
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    · -- `closure A` is included in `closure (interior A)` because `A ⊆ _`
      have : closure A ⊆ closure (interior A) := closure_mono hP1
      simpa using this
    · -- The reverse inclusion always holds
      have : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure A := by
        have : interior A ⊆ A := interior_subset
        exact closure_mono this
      simpa using this
  · intro hEq
    dsimp [Topology.P1]
    -- `A` is included in `closure (interior A)` via the equality of closures
    have : A ⊆ closure A := subset_closure
    have : A ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
      intro x hx
      have : x ∈ closure A := this hx
      simpa [hEq] using this
    exact this

theorem closed_P2_iff_P3 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA_closed : IsClosed A) :
    Topology.P2 A ↔ Topology.P3 A := by
  constructor
  · intro hP2
    exact Topology.P2_imp_P3 (X := X) (A := A) hP2
  · intro hP3
    have hA_open : IsOpen A :=
      Topology.closed_P3_isOpen (X := X) (A := A) hA_closed hP3
    exact Topology.isOpen_imp_P2 (X := X) (A := A) hA_open
